name: C70 Move the file to a folder using the context menu
fullName: C70 Move the file to a folder using the context menu

steps.name: Given User should be on the Home web page
And User should be on the Main web page and signed as "Phantom user"
Given user must be in the "Files" section
And any available file at the root
uncaught exception TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'constructor')
And any available folder at the root
log _> FILE: [cyA.Customer Configuration Producer] ~ created is Successful
When user clicks "Move" in the context menu of the target "File"
And user selects an available folder in modal form "Move file"
And user click on ["MOVE TO THIS FOLDER"] button in modal form "Move file"
Then this file has been successfully moved
assert expected **{ message: success }** to have property **message** of **success**
And this file should not be displayed in the active folder
And this file should be displayed in the selected folder
assert expected **<div.file__title.text--14.text--medium>** to exist in the DOM
